summary: An ordinance accepting the deposits made by the Seattle Electric Company under Ordinance No. 22719 entitled: "An ordinance granting to The Seattle Electric Company, its successors and assigns, franchise to construct, maintain and operate a street railway upon certain parts of Atlantic Street and Utah Street, and other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle" approved December 10, 1909, and published December 14, 1909; consenting to the acceptance of said ordinance by the Seattle Electric Company, and approving, ratifying and confirming the acts of the officials of the City of Seattle in filing said acceptance, in accepting said deposits and in granting the permit to construct the railway by said ordinance.
